This paper deals with the analysis of the condition number of Gaussian random matrices, which is a fundamental problem in numerical linear algebra. The paper provides bounds on the condition number and its expected value, which are important in the analysis of algorithms that involve matrix inversion or solving linear systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), which are also relevant to the analysis of matrices and linear systems. The paper also involves some probabilistic and statistical analysis, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) possible sub-categories, although less likely.
